abstract: Amid fears of computers crashing and cybersquatting, the Facebook land rush of 2009 appeared to go off without a hitch.
snippet: Amid fears of computers crashing and cybersquatting, the Facebook land rush of 2009 appeared to go off without a hitch.
lead_paragraph: Friday night, around 9:05 PST, I yelped and shot out of my seat, startling the guests at a dinner party in Oakland, Calif., and nearly knocking over a fresh bottle of Prosecco.

headline.main: Report From the Facebook Land Rush
